-- Russian finmin sold $500 million through cenbank on Dec 18
-- By Lidia Kelly and Vladimir Abramov
-- Mon Dec 22, 2014 02:03AM EST
-- None



MOSCOW, Dec 22 (Reuters) - The Russian central bank said on Monday it had conducted no interventions on the currency market on Dec. 18, but the Finance Ministry sold $500 million of foreign currency through the central bank.

